SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 45
BY SENATORS REESE, ALLAIN, CATHEY, FESI AND LUNEAU
CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences to the family and friends of
Allyce Trapp Alexander on the occasion of her passing.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere condolences of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the passing of
3 Allyce Trapp Alexander, and to celebrate her remarkable life, her service to the
4 people of Louisiana, and the love she shared with all who knew her.
5 WHEREAS, Allyce Trapp Alexander, age thirty-one, of Baton Rouge, Louisiana,
6 passed away peacefully on the morning of September 27, 2025, surrounded by the family
7 she cherished above all else; and
8 WHEREAS, Allyce was born on January 6, 1994, in Houma, Louisiana, to Heinke
9 and Susan Trapp, and grew up in a supportive, close-knit family that nurtured her
10 confidence, curiosity, and kindness; and
11 WHEREAS, a proud graduate of Vandebilt Catholic High School, Allyce was active
12 in student council, tennis, and volleyball, and was voted "Best Dressed" by her classmates
13 for her signature flair and impeccable style; and
14 WHEREAS, as a teenager, she was honored to serve as a Maid of Mardi Gras in the
15 Krewe of Houmas, reflecting her deep love for Louisiana's culture and traditions; and
16 WHEREAS, in 2012, Allyce moved to Baton Rouge to attend Louisiana State
17 University, where she joined Chi Omega sorority, oversaw a student government election
18 cycle, and earned both her bachelor's and master's degrees from the Manship School of Mass
