1 WHEREAS, in June 2024, Allyce was diagnosed with angiosarcoma, a rare and
2 aggressive cancer, and she faced the disease with extraordinary courage, faith, and
3 determination for sixteen months, inspiring all who walked beside her; and
4 WHEREAS, Allyce is survived by her beloved husband, Wilson Alexander; her
5 parents, Heinke and Susan Trapp; her brother, John Trapp; her maternal grandmother, Ann
6 Lirette; and numerous aunts, uncles, and cousins; and
7 WHEREAS, she was preceded in death by her grandparents Nolan Lirette Sr., Heinke
8 Trapp Sr., and Audrey Trapp, and she looked forward with faith to being reunited with them,
9 as well as her cherished pets Quasimodo and Sophie; and
10 WHEREAS, though her time on earth was far too short, Allyce herself said, "I've
11 lived a lot of life in 31 years. I have no complaints", a testament to her gratitude, resilience,
12 and joyful spirit; and
13 WHEREAS, Allyce's life was a blessing to her family, her friends, her colleagues,
14 and to the state she loved, and her memory will continue to inspire compassion, service, and
15 grace in all who knew her.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
17 extend its most sincere and deepest condolences to the family and friends of Allyce Trapp
18 Alexander and does hereby honor her life, her service, and her enduring legacy.
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that copies of this Resolution be transmitted to her
20 husband and parents.
